---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Nivedita Pandey">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <section class="bio">
      <h2>Bio</h2>
      <div class="bio-inner">
        <div class="bio-text">
          <p>
            I am a strategist and operator with 16+ years of international experience across the US, UK, Singapore, and India.
            My career follows an H-shaped trajectory across two pillars: digital innovation and go-to-market execution at scale.
            The connector across them is a cross-border ecosystem development approach that accelerates value creation.
            I work at the intersection of emerging technologies, institutional adoption, and ecosystem building—with
            particular focus on Applied AI, Private Capital, and Public Sector Transformation.
          </p>
          <p>
            I hold an MBA from Wharton and degrees in computer science and social impact. My career includes scaling Microsoft's
            PE/VC partnerships vertical across APAC to $130M, serving as a Prime Minister's Fellow on Digital Payments and Digital
            Public Infrastructure, and advising the Reserve Bank Innovation Hub on AI governance and DPI strategy.
          </p>
          <p>
            I currently run Dendrons.ai, an Applied AI Innovation Studio selected for Antler Singapore and Google Cloud for Startups.
            I also serve as Managing Director - Asia for Wharton Alumni Angels and lead SkillAI.academy, a training brand focused on
            AI governance and applied AI for institutions.
          </p>
          <p class="bio-contact">
            <a href="mailto:np@niveditapandey.com">np@niveditapandey.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio-photo-block">
          <img
            src="/images/about-bio.png"
            alt="Nivedita Pandey"
            class="bio-photo"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="work-on" id="work">
      <h2>What I Work On</h2>
      <div class="work-inner">
        <div class="work-text">
          <p>
            My work sits at the intersection of three domains:
          </p>
          <ul class="work-list">
            <li>
              <strong>Digital Innovation:</strong> Product strategy for emerging technologies, with recent focus on AI governance,
              digital public infrastructure, and healthcare coordination platforms.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Go-to-Market & Scale:</strong> Growth strategies, partnership development, and institutional sales—particularly
              in technology adoption by governments, financial institutions, and enterprise.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cross-Border Ecosystems:</strong> Building partnerships and market entry strategies across Asia-Pacific,
              connecting innovation ecosystems between India, Singapore, and global markets.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="work-photo-block">
          <img
            src="/images/about-ai.png"
            alt="At a technology conference"
            class="work-photo"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="beyond" id="beyond">
      <h2>Beyond Work</h2>
      <p>
        Outside of professional work, I have several deep interests that shape how I think and live.
      </p>

      <div class="beyond-grid">
        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Spirituality</h3>
          <p>
            I maintain a serious engagement with Vedic astrology, the Ramcharitmanas, and meditation practices. These aren't
            casual interests—they're frameworks I use to understand purpose, time, and uncertainty.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Animals & Rescue</h3>
          <p>
            I have a profound connection with animals, particularly cats. I support animal rescue work and believe in the
            responsibility we have toward creatures who cannot advocate for themselves.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Adventure Sports</h3>
          <img
            src="/images/beyond-adventure.png"
            alt="Rappelling"
            class="beyond-photo"
          />
          <p>
            To be added.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Travel & Curiosity</h3>
          <p>
            I've lived and worked across multiple continents, and I'm endlessly curious about how systems, cultures, and
            institutions work differently across contexts. Travel is less about tourism and more about pattern recognition.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Performing Arts</h3>
          <p>
            To be added.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 750px;
  }

  .about h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio-contact {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .bio-contact a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .work-list li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .work-list strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* Bio layout */
  .bio-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .bio-photo-block {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .bio-photo {
    width: 220px;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  /* Work on layout */
  .work-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .work-photo-block {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .work-photo {
    width: 220px;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  /* Beyond Work */
  .beyond-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .beyond-item h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .beyond-item p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .beyond-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 420px;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .bio-inner,
    .work-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .bio-photo-block,
    .work-photo-block {
      order: -1;
    }

    .bio-photo,
    .work-photo {
      width: 160px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }
</style>
